Adapted from a novel with the same title

&ldquo;Ride this, my beloved consort!&rdquo; Instantly rewarded with a punch in his charming face. He looked hurt, &ldquo;I just wanted you to try out the mythical beast mount!&rdquo;

Having died a cruel and excruciating death in her past incarnation, she was reborn into a body imbued with an impeccable talent for cultivation. A good-for-nothing? Fire, water, ice, wind, thunder, and nature; switching between the six elements is easy as pie. Supreme grade pills? She scatters them in the air like candies. Legendary beasts? They&rsquo;re begging her to form a contract. She is the arrogant Queen almighty! You say that heaven is undefiable? Then she will defy it!

&ldquo;Bad news, my Lord! The consort has beaten the Empress of the Heavenly Phoenix Nation into a pulp!&rdquo;
He raised an eyebrow and brimmed of pride, &ldquo;It&rsquo;s nothing. Send a million troops to back up my beloved consort. Tell them that I&rsquo;m the one who&rsquo;s pampering her!&rdquo;
